# Frontend Rules

## Next.js App Router
- Server Components by default — only add `'use client'` when you need browser APIs, event handlers, or React state
- Data fetching happens in Server Components via `async/await` — never `useEffect` for initial data
- Use `loading.tsx` for loading states, `error.tsx` for error boundaries in every route segment
- Images: always use `next/image` — never `<img>` tags

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline styles
- Mobile-first: write base styles for mobile, override at `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints
- Dark mode aware — use Tailwind `dark:` variants wherever relevant

## Components
- One component per file
- Props must be typed with an explicit TypeScript interface above the component
- Avoid prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use React Context or Zustand
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives (Button, Dialog, Input, etc.) — never modify files inside `components/ui/` directly

## State management
- Local UI state: `useState`
- Cart state: Zustand store at `store/cart.ts`
- Server state / caching: Next.js `fetch` with `revalidate`, not React Query (Phase 1)

## Forms
- react-hook-form + zod for all forms — no uncontrolled inputs
- Show field-level validation errors inline, not in toasts
